# GitHub Copilot Instructions for prixElek Project

## Language & Code Standards

**Primary Language:** English (100% for code)
- All variable names, function names, methods, comments in English
- French used only in documentation (doc/ folder)
- Exception: Comments explaining French business context may include French terms in parentheses

**Framework & Tools:**
- Frontend: React or Vue.js (decision in progress) with TypeScript
- Backend: Node.js + Express (if needed)
- Package Manager: npm (Windows PowerShell compatible)
- Code Style: ESLint + Prettier (strict mode)
- Testing: Jest + React Testing Library (or Vue Test Utils)

## Code Architecture

### Adapter Pattern (for Suppliers)
- Base class: `FournisseurAdapter` with abstract methods
- Each supplier: `RexelAdapter`, `SoneParAdapter`, YessAdapter`, `MaterielEltriqueAdapter`
- Location: `src/adapters/`
- Must implement: `authenticate(login, password)` and `getPrice(reference, token)`
- Return types: TypeScript interfaces for type safety

### Module Structure
- Each module in `src/modules/` follows MVC pattern
- Service layer handles business logic
- Components are reusable React/Vue components
- State management via Context API (React) or Pinia (Vue)

### Services Layer
- `PriceService` — orchestrates all adapter calls
- `CatalogService` — loads and manages catalogue.json
- `TokenService` — manages supplier tokens in localStorage
- `CacheService` — implements price caching with TTL

## Windows & Cross-Platform Requirements

### Path Handling
```typescript
import { join } from 'path';

// Always use
const configPath = join(process.cwd(), 'config', 'catalogue.json');

// Never hardcode paths with backslashes
// ❌ const path = "C:\\Users\\...";
```

### PowerShell Compatibility
- All npm scripts must work in PowerShell v5.1+
- Use forward slashes in npm scripts (package.json)
- Document all commands in PowerShell syntax in README

### Environment Variables
- Use `.env` files (never `.env.local` committed to git)
- Document in `.env.example`
- Access via: `process.env.VARIABLE_NAME`

## Security Requirements

### Token Storage
```typescript
// Tokens must NEVER be:
// - Logged to console
// - Stored in version control
// - Sent to external servers
// - Hardcoded in code

// Correct approach:
const tokenStore = {
  save: (supplierId: string, token: string) => {
    localStorage.setItem(`prixelek_token_${supplierId}`, token);
  },
  get: (supplierId: string): string | null => {
    return localStorage.getItem(`prixelek_token_${supplierId}`);
  },
  clear: (supplierId: string) => {
    localStorage.removeItem(`prixelek_token_${supplierId}`);
  }
};
```

### Configuration Files
- `config/catalogue.json` — OK to commit (public data)
- `config/fournisseurs.json` — ❌ NEVER commit (contains tokens)
- Add to `.gitignore`:
  ```
  config/fournisseurs.json
  .env
  .env.local
  *.log
  dist/
  node_modules/
  ```

## Error Handling

### Adapter Error Types
```typescript
interface FetchError {
  code: 'AUTH_ERROR' | 'NETWORK_ERROR' | 'NOT_FOUND' | 'RATE_LIMIT' | 'TIMEOUT';
  supplierId: string;
  message: string;
  statusCode?: number;
  retryable: boolean;
}

// Example usage
if (error.code === 'AUTH_ERROR') {
  // Notify user to reconnect
}
if (error.retryable && retryCount < 3) {
  // Implement exponential backoff
}
```

### Request Limits
- Minimum 500ms between supplier API calls
- Timeouts: 10 seconds per request
- Max 3 retries with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s)
- Rate limit detection: 429 status → back off for 60 seconds

## Component Guidelines

### React Components (if selected)
```typescript
// Use functional components with hooks
// Export with TypeScript interfaces for props
interface PriceTableProps {
  materials: Material[];
  suppliers: Supplier[];
  loading: boolean;
  onRefresh: () => Promise<void>;
}

// Use custom hooks for shared logic
const usePriceComparison = () => {
  // implementation
};

// Export default
export default PriceTable;
```

### Vue Components (if selected)
```typescript
// Use Composition API with TypeScript
// Define types before template
// Use reactive() for state
// Use computed() for derived state
```

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests
- Coverage minimum: 80%
- Test all adapter methods
- Mock external API calls
- Location: `src/__tests__/`

### Example Test Structure
```typescript
describe('RexelAdapter', () => {
  let adapter: RexelAdapter;

  beforeEach(() => {
    adapter = new RexelAdapter();
  });

  test('authenticate should return token on success', async () => {
    // Test implementation
  });

  test('getPrice should return price object on success', async () => {
    // Test implementation
  });

  test('should retry on network error', async () => {
    // Test implementation
  });
});
```

## Documentation Standards

### Code Comments
```typescript
/**
 * Fetches and caches prices for all materials from a specific supplier
 * @param supplierId - Identifier of the supplier (e.g., 'rexel', 'sonepar')
 * @param token - Authentication token from localStorage
 * @returns Promise resolving to array of prices
 * @throws {FetchError} If API call fails after 3 retries
 * @example
 * const prices = await priceService.fetchPrices('rexel', token);
 */
async fetchPrices(supplierId: string, token: string): Promise<Price[]> {
  // implementation
}
```

### File Headers
```typescript
/**
 * src/adapters/rexel.ts
 * 
 * Rexel supplier adapter for price fetching
 * Handles authentication and product price retrieval via Rexel API
 * 
 * @module adapters/rexel
 * @since 1.0.0
 */
```

## Git Workflow

### Commit Messages
```
feat(adapters): implement Rexel adapter with bearer token auth
fix(service): correct cache invalidation on price refresh
docs(cdc-m1): clarify price comparison requirements
chore(deps): upgrade axios to 1.6.0

Format: type(scope): subject
```

### Branch Naming
```
feature/adapter-rexel
bugfix/token-expiration
docs/windows-setup
```

## Debugging on Windows

### VS Code Debug Configuration
```json
{
  "version": "0.2.0",
  "configurations": [
    {
      "type": "node",
      "request": "launch",
      "name": "prixElek Debug",
      "program": "${workspaceFolder}/src/index.ts",
      "runtimeArgs": ["--loader", "ts-node/esm"],
      "console": "integratedTerminal"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Chrome DevTools for Adapter Discovery
- Press F12 to open DevTools
- Network tab → Filter by Fetch/XHR
- Check "Preserve log"
- Log in to supplier website
- Inspect requests to find API endpoints
- Copy as fetch request
- Document in `doc/scraping.md`

## Performance Targets

- Initial page load: < 3 seconds
- Price refresh: < 5 seconds (with 4 suppliers)
- Price cache TTL: 15 minutes
- Search/filter responsiveness: < 100ms

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements accessible via keyboard
- ARIA labels for dynamic content
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1
- Focus indicators visible

## Release Checklist

- [ ] All tests passing (npm run test)
- [ ] No linting errors (npm run lint)
- [ ] No console errors/warnings
- [ ] .env and credentials files in .gitignore
- [ ] Windows paths tested
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Git commit messages follow format

---

**Version:** 1.0  
**Last Updated:** 2026-03-18  
**Maintained by:** prixElek Team

/**
 * src/App.tsx
 */
import React, { useCallback, useState } from 'react';
import { usePriceScan } from '@/hooks/usePriceScan';
import { useCatalogue } from '@/hooks/useCatalogue';
import { useCommande } from '@/hooks/useCommande';
import { useRexelAuth } from '@/hooks/useRexelAuth';
import { PriceTable } from '@/components/PriceTable';
import { CatalogueToolbar } from '@/components/CatalogueToolbar';
import { CommandeTab } from '@/components/CommandeTab';
import { EditMaterialModal } from '@/components/EditMaterialModal';
import { AddFromUrlModal } from '@/components/AddFromUrlModal';
import { RexelLoginModal } from '@/components/RexelLoginModal';
import type { Material, Catalog } from '@/types/material';

type Tab = 'catalogue' | 'commande';

export function App(): React.ReactElement {
  const {
    materials,
    importCatalogue,
    addMaterial,
    updateMaterial,
    removeMaterial,
    exportCatalogue,
  } = useCatalogue();
  const { prices, scanning, startScan, stopScan } = usePriceScan();
  const rexelAuth = useRexelAuth();
  const commande = useCommande();
  const { selectedIds, toggleSelected, setAllSelected } = commande;

  // Tabs
  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState<Tab>('catalogue');

  // Pass rexel token and selected ids to scan — only fetch prices for order items
  const handleScan = useCallback(
    () => startScan(materials, rexelAuth.token, selectedIds.size > 0 ? selectedIds : undefined),
    [startScan, materials, rexelAuth.token, selectedIds]
  );

  // Edit modal
  const [editingMaterial, setEditingMaterial] = useState<Material | null>(null);

  // Add-from-URL modal
  const [showAddModal, setShowAddModal] = useState(false);

  // Rexel login modal
  const [showRexelModal, setShowRexelModal] = useState(false);

  const toolbar = (
    <CatalogueToolbar
      onImport={(items: Catalog) => importCatalogue(items)}
      onExport={exportCatalogue}
      onAddFromUrl={() => setShowAddModal(true)}
    />
  );

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
      {/* ── Header ── */}
      <header className="bg-white border-b border-gray-200 px-6 py-4">
        <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between">
          <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span className="text-2xl">⚡</span>
            <div>
              <h1 className="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">prixElek</h1>
              <p className="text-sm text-gray-500">Comparateur de prix fournisseurs</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Supplier connection status */}
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
            <button
              onClick={() => setShowRexelModal(true)}
              className={[
                'inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-xs font-medium border transition-colors',
                rexelAuth.isConnected
                  ? 'bg-green-50 border-green-200 text-green-700 hover:bg-green-100'
                  : 'bg-gray-50 border-gray-200 text-gray-500 hover:bg-gray-100',
              ].join(' ')}
            >
              {rexelAuth.isConnected ? '' : ''}
              Rexel
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      {/* ── Tabs ── */}
      <div className="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
        <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
          <nav className="flex gap-1 -mb-px" aria-label="Onglets">
            <button
              onClick={() => setActiveTab('catalogue')}
              className={[
                'px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium border-b-2 transition-colors',
                activeTab === 'catalogue'
                  ? 'border-orange-500 text-orange-600'
                  : 'border-transparent text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-700 hover:border-gray-300',
              ].join(' ')}
            >
               Catalogue
            </button>
            <button
              onClick={() => setActiveTab('commande')}
              className={[
                'px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium border-b-2 transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-2',
                activeTab === 'commande'
                  ? 'border-orange-500 text-orange-600'
                  : 'border-transparent text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-700 hover:border-gray-300',
              ].join(' ')}
            >
               Commande
              {selectedIds.size > 0 && (
                <span className="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-5 h-5 rounded-full text-xs font-bold bg-orange-500 text-white">
                  {selectedIds.size}
                </span>
              )}
            </button>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* ── Main content ── */}
      <main className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-8">
        {activeTab === 'catalogue' && (
          <PriceTable
            materials={materials}
            prices={prices}
            scanning={scanning}
            onScan={handleScan}
            onStop={stopScan}
            onEdit={(m) => setEditingMaterial(m)}
            toolbar={toolbar}
            selectedIds={selectedIds}
            onToggleSelect={toggleSelected}
            onToggleSelectAll={setAllSelected}
          />
        )}
        {activeTab === 'commande' && (
          <CommandeTab materials={materials} prices={prices} commande={commande} />
        )}
      </main>

      {/* ── Modals ── */}
      {editingMaterial && (
        <EditMaterialModal
          material={editingMaterial}
          onSave={updateMaterial}
          onDelete={removeMaterial}
          onClose={() => setEditingMaterial(null)}
        />
      )}
      {showAddModal && (
        <AddFromUrlModal onAdd={addMaterial} onClose={() => setShowAddModal(false)} />
      )}
      {showRexelModal && (
        <RexelLoginModal
          currentToken={rexelAuth.token}
          onSave={rexelAuth.saveToken}
          onClear={rexelAuth.clearToken}
          onClose={() => setShowRexelModal(false)}
        />
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

